  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN178.1-kilavi">tōḻi varaivu malintu colliyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">What the confidante said when rejoicing in the marriage.</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="AN178.1">
        <l>vayirat taṉṉa vaiyēntu maruppiṉ</l>
        <l>vetirvē raṉṉa parūumayirp paṉṟi</l>
        <l>paṟaikka ṇaṉṉa niṟaiccuṉai paruki</l>
        <l>nilakka ṇaṉṉa vakalilaic cēmpiṉ</l>
        <l>piṇṭa maṉṉa koḻuṅkiḻaṅku māntip</l>
        <l>piṭimaṭin taṉṉa kaṉmicai yūḻiḻipu</l>
        <l>yāṟucērn taṉṉa vūṟunīrp paṭarā<del>m</del></l>
        <l>paim<supplied>puta</supplied> ṉaḷiciṉaik<anchor n="1"/> kurukirun taṉṉa</l>
        <l>vaṇpiṇi yaviḻnta veṇkū tāḷat</l>
        <l>talaṅkukulai yalari tīṇṭit tātukap</l>
        <l>poṉṉurai kaṭṭaḷai kaṭuppak kāṉavar</l>
        <l>kiḷaiyamal <supplied>ciṟu</supplied>tiṉai viḷaikura<supplied>ṉ</supplied> mēyntu</l>
        <l>kaṇṇiṉitu paṭukku naṉmalai nāṭaṉoṭu</l>
        <l>nērntaṉai puṇarnta nīyu niṉṟōṭ</l>
        <l>paṇaikkavi ṉaḻiyātu<del>t</del> tuṇaippuṇarn teṉavan</l>
        <l>takavali lulakat tuṟaiyarō tōḻi</l>
        <l>yellaiyu miravu meṉṉātu kalleṉak</l>
        <l>koṇṭal va<supplied>ḷa</supplied>mpoḻinta kuḷirkoḷ vaikaṟait</l>
        <l>taṇpaṉi yacciran tamiyōrk kariteṉak<anchor n="2"/></l>
        <l>kaṉaviṉum pirivaṟi yalaṉē yataṉṟalai</l>
        <l>muṟṟāṉ kaṇṭa ñāṉṟiṉum</l>
        <l>piṟperi taḷikkuntaṉ paṇpi ṉāṉē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>With the man from the land of good mountains, where (13cd)</l>
        <l>the pigs with hair coarse like bamboo roots(2)</l>
        <l>[and] sharp upright tusks like clubs (1)</l>
        <l>drink from mountain pools full like the eyes of drums, (3)</l>
        <l>feed on the rich bulbous roots like on lumps of rice (5)</l>
        <l>of the Cēmpu with leaves broad like patches of ground, (4)</l>
        <l>descend in turn from the height of boulders that are like dozing elephant cows, (6)</l>
        <l>without thinking of the water that drizzles as if from a river, (7)</l>
        <l>grip, so that pollen is shed, the flowers on the swaying bunches (10)</l>
        <l>of the white Convolvulus that had opened [its] generous outer petals, (9)</l>
        <l>like herons perched on the dense branches of fresh bushes, (8)</l>
        <l>graze on the ripening ears of the densely branching little millet (12)</l>
        <l>of the forest people, resembling gold-grating touch stones, (11)</l>
        <l rend="indent8">[and] pleasantly close [their] eyes, (13ab)</l>
        <l>you have agreed, you who united [with him], and, since your shoulder (14)</l>
        <l>did not lose [its] bamboo beauty because [you] were united with [your] mate, (15)</l>
        <l>won’t he come [and] stay in a world that is within calling [distance], friend? (16)</l>
        <l>Since the season of cool dew is difficult for those who are alone, (19)</l>
        <l>at cold dawn when the clouds have showered [their] wealth (18)</l>
        <l>noisily, without heeding day or night, (17)</l>
        <l>he won’t know of separation anymore than a dream. Moreover, (20)</l>
        <l>more than in the time he has seen [you] before (21)</l>
        <l>one of his nature will well take care [of you] later on. (22)</l>
      </lg>
        </div>
